# Spring Boot 2.7 to 3.2 POM Migration Skill

## Overview
Migrating a Maven project from Spring Boot 2.7.x to 3.2.x requires updating the parent POM, Java version, and several dependencies.

## Key Changes

### Parent POM
"'```xml
<parent>
    <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>
    <artifactId>spring-boot-starter-parent</artifactId>
    <version>3.2.0</version>
    <relativePath/>
</parent>
```

### Java Version
```xml
<properties>
    <java.version>21</java.version>
</properties>
```

### JJWT Migration
Old single artifact `jjwt:0.9.x` must be replaced with modular JJWT 0.12.x:
```xml
<dependency>
    <groupId>io.jsonwebtoken</groupId>
    <artifactId>jjwt-api</artifactId>
    <version>0.12.6</version>
</dependency>
<dependency>
    <groupId>io.jsonwebtoken</groupId>
    <artifactId>jjwt-impl</artifactId>
    <version>0.12.6</version>
    <scope>runtime</scope>
</dependency>
<dependency>
    <groupId>io.jsonwebtoken</groupId>
    <artifactId>jjwt-jackson</artifactId>
    <version>0.12.6</version>
    <scope>runtime</scope>
</dependency>
```

### Remove javax.xml.bind:jaxb-api
No longer needed with Java 21 and modern JJWT. Remove entirely.

### Spring Boot Starters
Starters like `spring-boot-starter-web`, `spring-boot-starter-data-jpa`, `spring-boot-starter-validation`, `spring-boot-starter-security` are managed by the parent POM — no version changes needed for these.

## Maven Compiler Plugin
Spring Boot 3.2 parent POM handles the compiler plugin configuration via `<java.version>` property.
