# Spring Security 6 Migration Skill

## Overview
Spring Security 6 (used in Spring Boot 3.x) removes "'`WebSecurityConfigurerAdapter` and several deprecated methods.

## Key Changes

### 1. Remove WebSecurityConfigurerAdapter
Replace class-based configuration with component-based `@Bean` methods.

### 2. @EnableGlobalMethodSecurity → @EnableMethodSecurity
```java
// Before
@EnableGlobalMethodSecurity(prePostEnabled = true)

// After
@EnableMethodSecurity  // prePostEnabled=true is the default
```

### 3. SecurityFilterChain Bean
```java
@Bean
public SecurityFilterChain securityFilterChain(HttpSecurity http) throws Exception {
    http
        .csrf(csrf -> csrf.disable())
        .sessionManagement(session -> session.sessionCreationPolicy(SessionCreationPolicy.STATELESS))
        .authorizeHttpRequests(auth -> auth
            .requestMatchers(HttpMethod.POST, "/api/users").permitAll()
            .requestMatchers("/api/auth/**").permitAll()
            .anyRequest().authenticated()
        );
    return http.build();
}
```

### 4. antMatchers → requestMatchers
All `antMatchers()`, `mvcMatchers()`, `regexMatchers()` are replaced by `requestMatchers()`.

### 5. authorizeRequests → authorizeHttpRequests
The old `authorizeRequests()` is replaced by `authorizeHttpRequests()`.

### 6. Lambda DSL
Spring Security 6 prefers lambda DSL for configuration:
```java
http.csrf(csrf -> csrf.disable())
    .headers(headers -> headers.frameOptions(frame -> frame.disable()))
```

### 7. AuthenticationManager Bean
```java
@Bean
public AuthenticationManager authenticationManager(AuthenticationConfiguration config) throws Exception {
    return config.getAuthenticationManager();
}
```

### 8. UserDetailsService + PasswordEncoder
When both beans are present, Spring Security auto-configures the `DaoAuthenticationProvider`.
