# RestTemplate to RestClient Migration Skill

## Overview
Spring Boot 3.2 introduces "'`RestClient` as a modern, fluent replacement for `RestTemplate`.
`RestClient` provides a synchronous HTTP client with a fluent API similar to `WebClient`.

## Creating a RestClient
```java
import org.springframework.web.client.RestClient;

// Simple creation
RestClient restClient = RestClient.create();

// With base URL
RestClient restClient = RestClient.builder()
    .baseUrl("https://api.example.com")
    .build();
```

## Common Operations

### GET Request
```java
// Before (RestTemplate)
ResponseEntity<Map> response = restTemplate.getForEntity(url, Map.class);

// After (RestClient)
Map result = restClient.get()
    .uri("/verify/email?email={email}", email)
    .retrieve()
    .body(Map.class);
```

### POST Request
```java
// Before (RestTemplate)
restTemplate.postForEntity(url, request, Void.class);

// After (RestClient)
restClient.post()
    .uri("/notifications")
    .contentType(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)
    .body(payload)
    .retrieve()
    .toBodilessEntity();
```

### Exchange (GET with headers)
```java
// Before (RestTemplate)
ResponseEntity<Map> response = restTemplate.exchange(url, HttpMethod.GET, request, Map.class);

// After (RestClient)
Map result = restClient.get()
    .uri("/users/{id}/profile", userId)
    .accept(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)
    .retrieve()
    .body(Map.class);
```

### DELETE Request
```java
// Before (RestTemplate)
restTemplate.delete(url);

// After (RestClient)
restClient.delete()
    .uri("/users/{id}/data", userId)
    .retrieve()
    .toBodilessEntity();
```

## Error Handling
Wrap calls in try-catch as before. `RestClient` throws `RestClientException` subtypes on HTTP errors.
