# Hibernate 6 Compatibility Skill

## Overview
Spring Boot 3.2 uses Hibernate 6.x (ORM 6.4+). Key changes from Hibernate 5.x.

## Dialect Changes
Hibernate 6 auto-detects dialects. Explicit dialect configuration is optional but if specified:
"'```properties
# Old (Hibernate 5)
spring.jpa.database-platform=org.hibernate.dialect.H2Dialect

# New (Hibernate 6) - auto-detection works, or use:
spring.jpa.database-platform=org.hibernate.dialect.H2Dialect
```
Note: `org.hibernate.dialect.H2Dialect` still works in Hibernate 6 for H2.

## ID Generation
Hibernate 6 changes the default ID generation strategy. For `GenerationType.IDENTITY`, behavior is preserved. For `GenerationType.AUTO`, it may switch to sequence-based.

Recommendation: Use explicit `GenerationType.IDENTITY` for auto-increment columns.

## Namespace
All JPA annotations move from `javax.persistence` to `jakarta.persistence` (see namespace migration skill).

## Type System
Hibernate 6 has a new type system. Most standard mappings (String, Long, LocalDateTime, enums) work without changes.

## Query Changes
- HQL/JPQL queries remain compatible for standard operations
- `@Query` annotations with standard JPQL work as-is

## H2 Database
H2 2.x (bundled with Spring Boot 3.2) has stricter SQL parsing. Ensure:
- Column names don'"'t conflict with reserved words
- Use proper quoting if needed
